# Agent Prompt Templates

These are copy-paste prompts for invoking agents at each stage of the pipeline.
Replace `<ISSUE_NUMBER>`, `<AGENT>`, and bracketed placeholders before using.

---

## Pipeline Overview

```
New Issue Found → Backlog (auto) → [PM: Ready] → [Dev: In Progress] → [Dev: In Review]
→ [QA: Done or back to In Progress] → [DevOps: confirm or back to In Progress]
→ [Docs: Closed]
```

**Any agent finding a side issue must create a `gh issue` and add it to the Backlog before continuing.**

---

## 1. Incidental Issue (any agent)

> Use this when you discover a bug or gap while working on something else.

```
You are the [AGENT NAME] for the Pigskin Fantasy Football Auction Draft System.

While working on issue #<ORIGINAL_ISSUE>, you found the following problem:
<describe the problem>

Follow the Incidental Issue Protocol from `.agents/AGENT_MANAGER.md`:
1. Create a gh issue for this finding
2. Add it to the project backlog
3. Resume work on issue #<ORIGINAL_ISSUE>

Do not fix the incidental issue now unless it is a P0 blocker for your current task.
```

